description:
#VEGAN Pork Sinigang sa Rattan fruit. For the “pork,” I used meat magic, and the “fat” is made of tapioca starch, rice flour, and agar. For the broth, it’s soured by rattan fruit. Have you heard of it? It has a sour flavor with hints of sweetness, like green tamarind. I also used mushroom broth for the umami. And, of course, lots of veggies. Very comforting soup!

For the Sinigang recipe, it’s in the book, “Filipino Vegan,” and for the “pork” recipe, it’s on my recorded livestream on Facebook (in the Nilaga episode). 

Kain na, let’s eat! 

#astigvegan #filipinofood #filipinovegan #veganfilipino
